        <div class="body">
            <p>That's correct behavior.</p>

<p>Standard PDF fonts support only Latin1 character set (actually some superset of Latin1 CS), even input string fro text drawing is represented in 'UTF-8' or any other encoding.
Appropriate TTF fonts should be used for other character sets.</p>

<p>I've just registered it as a Documentation improvment issue (<a href="http://framework.zend.com/issues/browse/ZF-3650">ZF-3650</a>).</p>

